## Segmental phonetics and phonemes {#sec:segmental}
The consonant phonemes of Yawarana are shown in <a href='#tab:consonants' class='crossref' id='tab:consonants'>crossref</a>, and the vowels in <a href='#tab:vowels' class='crossref' id='tab:vowels'>crossref</a>.
This is a fairly standard Cariban phoneme inventory, only departing from the mainstream by the addition of [Phoneme ch](PhonemeTable?#cldf:ch).


<a id='tab:consonants'></a><div class='caption table' id='tab:consonants'>Consonant phonemes</div>

|           | bilabial                          | alveolar                          | palatal                             | velar                             | glottal                           |
|:----------|:----------------------------------|:----------------------------------|:------------------------------------|:----------------------------------|:----------------------------------|
| occlusive | [Phoneme p](PhonemeTable?#cldf:p) | [Phoneme t](PhonemeTable?#cldf:t) | [Phoneme ch](PhonemeTable?#cldf:ch) | [Phoneme k](PhonemeTable?#cldf:k) |                                   |
| nasal     | [Phoneme m](PhonemeTable?#cldf:m) | [Phoneme n](PhonemeTable?#cldf:n) | [Phoneme J](PhonemeTable?#cldf:J)   |                                   |                                   |
| fricative |                                   | [Phoneme s](PhonemeTable?#cldf:s) |                                     |                                   | [Phoneme j](PhonemeTable?#cldf:j) |
| liquid    |                                   | [Phoneme r](PhonemeTable?#cldf:r) |                                     |                                   |                                   |
| glide     | [Phoneme w](PhonemeTable?#cldf:w) |                                   | [Phoneme y](PhonemeTable?#cldf:y)   |                                   |                                   |


