## Pronouns {#sec:pronouns}
The personal pronouns of [Language yab](LanguageTable?#cldf:yab) are shown in <a href='#tab:pronouns' class='crossref' id='tab:pronouns'>crossref</a>.
It shows the usual Cariban inclusive/exclusive (<span class=""smallcaps"">1+2</span> and <span class=""smallcaps"">1+3</span>) distinction. <span title='is the 1+2 form cognate with apina? do we know something about its etymology?'>❓</span>
Note that the plural marker [Morpheme kontomopl](MorphsetTable?#cldf:kontomopl) appears to usually be restricted to verbs, while *-santomo* is found with third person pronouns and demonstratives.


