### Argument prefixes {#sec:nominalperson}
Person prefixes on nouns are conditioned by the initial segment (<a href='#tab:possprefixes' class='crossref' id='tab:possprefixes'>crossref</a>).
C-initial nouns take third person [Morph i31](MorphTable?#cldf:i31), and first and second person are bare [Morph u1](MorphTable?#cldf:u1) and [Morph me2](MorphTable?#cldf:me2).
On V-initial nouns, third person is marked by [Morph it3](MorphTable?#cldf:it3), and first and second person combine with the linker [Morpheme ylk](MorphsetTable?#cldf:ylk).
Some examples are shown in <a class=""exref"" example_id=""ctorat-23""end=""ctorat-19"" ></a>.


<a id='tab:possprefixes'></a><div class='caption table' id='tab:possprefixes'>Possessive prefixes on nouns</div>

|                                  | _C                                | _V                                                                 |
|:---------------------------------|:----------------------------------|:-------------------------------------------------------------------|
| <span class=""smallcaps"">1</span> | [Morph u1](MorphTable?#cldf:u1)   | [Morph u1](MorphTable?#cldf:u1)[Morph ylk](MorphTable?#cldf:ylk)   |
| <span class=""smallcaps"">2</span> | [Morph me2](MorphTable?#cldf:me2) | [Morph me2](MorphTable?#cldf:me2)[Morph ylk](MorphTable?#cldf:ylk) |
| <span class=""smallcaps"">3</span> | [Morph i31](MorphTable?#cldf:i31) | [Morph it3](MorphTable?#cldf:it3)                                  |

