* Absolutive proclitics 
    * <span title='Check: appears that they are reduced forms, with long vowel? FM: i noticed a long vowel in convrisamaj-02'>❓</span>
    * [Morpheme u1](MorphsetTable?#cldf:u1) ‘1S/O’ <span title='is this ever actually *wï-*?'>❓</span>
    * [Morpheme me2](MorphsetTable?#cldf:me2) ‘2S/O’
        * one example of (më=) ‘2A’ on imperative verb <span title='where?'>❓</span>
* Third person
    * Ø‑ ‘3S’ with intransitive verbs
    *   • exception: *ij‑të‑ri* ‘he goes’ plus 2 more <span title='which ones?'>❓</span>
    * Ø‑ ‘3O’ with transitive verbs with 1A or 2A; also sometimes 3A
    * [Morpheme t3](MorphsetTable?#cldf:t3) ‘3A3O’
        * Not required, but possible
            * Check: not in alternation with preceding O NP?
        * [Morpheme t3](MorphsetTable?#cldf:t3) ‘3O’ attested on one V in the pan‑Cariban “progressive” construction w/ 2nd person A <span title='which one?'>❓</span>
* Note that all transitive verbs are consonant‑initial, whether etymologically or not because [Morpheme ylk](MorphsetTable?#cldf:ylk) ‘rel’ is added to all vowel‑initial roots
    * the _y‑_ disappears when preceded by the detransitivizer <span title='examples for detransitivized verbs'>❗️</span>

