ambiguity,Manuscript: Parsing ambiguity,"# Introduction <a id='sec:intro'></a>

* [Language yab](LanguageTable?#cldf:yab) ([yaba1248](https://glottolog.org/resource/languoid/id/yaba1248)) is an underdescribed Cariban language of Venezuela.
* [matter2022uniparser](sources.bib?with_internal_ref_link&ref#cldf:matter2022uniparser) is a morphological parser for [Language yab](LanguageTable?#cldf:yab), implemented with [uniparser-morph](https://github.com/timarkh/uniparser-morph)
* for many forms, the parser suggests multiple possible analyses
* this paper discusses these ambiguous forms, the reasons behind them, and the implemented solutions

# uniparser-morph

* something about uniparser-morph

## uniparser-yawarana

## Analysis elimination mechanisms

* bad analyses

* CG3 rules

# The ambiguities

## Accidental
* *makë*: 'mother' or ma-kë 'throw!'
* *yaka*: 'excavate' or 'ALL'
* *ma*: 'throw-NMLZ' or 'RESTR'?
    * safe to remove it after [Form 3b92fde8-f646-47dd-b190-18c1ca2d60791](FormTable?#cldf:3b92fde8-f646-47dd-b190-18c1ca2d60791): `REMOVE (""ma"" vt) IF (-1 (""tawara""));` 
* syllable reduction leads to homophonous [Morpheme 55db3ac7-4711-4980-845e-4b966dff41bc](MorphsetTable?#cldf:55db3ac7-4711-4980-845e-4b966dff41bc) and [Morpheme ccb970b7-980c-4dc2-84fc-f291fd9a6bab](MorphsetTable?#cldf:ccb970b7-980c-4dc2-84fc-f291fd9a6bab)
* [Morpheme teloc](MorphsetTable?#cldf:teloc) and [Morpheme a5589c54-8bcd-40e2-9d28-b29f1592ccd3](MorphsetTable?#cldf:a5589c54-8bcd-40e2-9d28-b29f1592ccd3)
* [Morpheme yakaall](MorphsetTable?#cldf:yakaall) and [Morpheme 02b332df-f7da-4749-9720-574666e70d71](MorphsetTable?#cldf:02b332df-f7da-4749-9720-574666e70d71) and [Morpheme 75b2df1a-11a1-44ad-8e38-88a6acf07322](MorphsetTable?#cldf:75b2df1a-11a1-44ad-8e38-88a6acf07322)
